doctemplate (2.5.0.1) raring; urgency=low

  * Add optional support for running postprocessing script in docbook phase
    of build, as follows:
    - Your customization branch (the one pointed to by the CUSTOM variable the
      project 'environment' file must export DBSCRIPT variable whose value
      is script name in CUSTOM/docbook-customization/. For example:
      if environment has these:
      export CUSTOM=../customization-brochure
      export DBSCRIPT=brochure.sh
      Then the following must exist:
      ../customization-brochure/docbook-customization/brochure.sh
    - That file "brochure.sh" is executed after the normal docbook phase. It may
      1) run another xsl transform on the normal generated end file of the
      docbook transform: build/docbook//LINGUA/DOC.xml generating a new file doc
      2) rename the new files so the new generated doc is named
      build/docbook//LINGUA/DOC.xml
    - note that the script is passed three arguments in the following order:
      1) the path to the customization dir (as defined in the project environment file)
      2) the path to the current docbook build dir, including linguage, for example:
      build/docbook/fr/
      3) the name of the project's root content doc (withoout the .xml extension)
      as defined in the project environment file.
    - A sample DBSCRIPT:
      #!/bin/bash
      set -e
      CUSTOM=$1
      BDOCBOOK=$2
      DOC=$3
      xsltproc \
          --stringparam showSlideTitles yes \
          -o $BDOCBOOK/book.custom.xml \
          $CUSTOM/docbook-customization/brochure.xsl \
          $BDOCBOOK/$DOC.xml
      # back up initial state of book.xml
      cp $BDOCBOOK/book.xml build/docbook/en/book.xml.orig
      mv $BDOCBOOK/book.custom.xml $BDOCBOOK/book.xml
      exit

 -- Kyle Nitzsche <kyle.nitzsche@canonical.com>  Fri, 26 Jul 2013 15:36:15 -0400

