    in the README file.

 -- Kyle Nitzsche <kyle.nitzsche@canonical.com>  Tue, 01 Mar 2011 15:22:01 -0500

doctemplate (1.9.14) maverick; urgency=low

  * Remove article customization directories from new article projects. Instead,
    the article's environment file now defines a variable (CUSTOM) that
    provides the path to the dir that contains the required customization
    layers. This allows one to make a customization and use it for any
    article, instead of having to make the customization in each and every
    article. The default/expected location for this directory is a sibling
    directory to the article itself: <article>/../customization. The
    doctemplate_setup_setup_article script now checks whether this directory
    exists and prompts the user to find out whether it should be created.

 -- Kyle Nitzsche <kyle.nitzsche@canonical.com>  Tue, 01 Mar 2011 15:07:38 -0500

