doctemplate (1.9.11) maverick; urgency=low

  * Enable user to override default apache font config by adding dt_fontconfig
    script to project dir. They can copy this script and pick up the default
    font configurations from /usr/bin/dt_fontconfig. Note that adding a font 
    configuration involves creating a conf file in 
    <project>/lib/apache/<font>.conf that points to fop xml files. At the
    moment, for examples look at the doctemplate font config files in
    /usr/share/doctemplate/libe/apache.

